text: Euclautubba Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. It is a tributary to Mud Creek. Euclautubba is a name derived from either the Choctaw language or Chickasaw language purported to mean either "“killer of people" or "the one who captures and kills". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Lee County, Mississippi
title: Euclautubba Creek
